message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Brazil, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you have the time, walking can be a good option. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take you around 3-5 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Public transportation: Depending on the availability of public transportation in your area, you can check for bus routes that pass near the grocery store. Use a transportation app or website to find the nearest bus stop and the appropriate bus route.

4. Taxi or rideshare: If you prefer a more comfortable and direct option, you can call a taxi or use a ridesharing app like Uber or 99. This will provide you with a door-to-door service, but it may be more expensive than other options.

Consider the time, weather conditions, and your personal preferences when choosing the best mode of transportation to reach the grocery store.
